2125 Hylan Boulevard, west side, at the head of Zwicky Avenue showing the South Shore Post, Veterans of Foreign Wars. The view from Zwicky Avenue. It was formerly the Hotel Del-Wit and was ow: by Chas. E. Spruck (1917 map). Prior to that it was called the Hotel Boulevard (1907 map).

May 26, 1935
P.L. Sperr
